Yesterday (Easter Sunday) was the first time ordering from The Yummy Kitchen. I ordered the combination beef & broccoli platter (came with pork fried rice and an egg roll). On the whole, my meal was edible yet underwhelming. My friend ordered the chicken and beef teriyaki with fried rice and two spring rolls. He loves teriyaki but  he's not a fan of their chicken and beef teriyaki. Being first-time patrons of The Yummy Kitchen, we felt blind-sided when the lady on the phone told me AFTER taking our food order that for FIRST-TIME customers they only accept cash or Apple Pay. This was not stated nor specified on their handout menu. On The Yummy Kitchen handout menu we'd received, it listed the credit cards that The Yummy Kitchen accepted: Visa, Mastercard, Discover. We were ready to pay for our meal with a credit card when the lady surprised me with the 'first-time customer/ cash/Apple Pay payment requirement'. We felt that was misleading and not in good faith. Needless to say, my friend and I will not be patronizing The Yummy Kitchen in the foreseeable future.
The fish and vegetables are always fresh and delicious. I started eating here when I found it on UberEats. Now, I live down the street.
